Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.97,0:00:06.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've noticed, have you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.10,0:00:08.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Butts?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.00,0:00:11.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong! The Jiggle Butt Gang!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.22,0:00:13.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you guys want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.15,0:00:16.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come on, do you know where we are?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.46,0:00:18.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.25,0:00:21.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jail! We're in a jail!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.20,0:00:23.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you in for, laddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.97,0:00:25.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.86,0:00:27.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.75,0:00:29.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Lucy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.64,0:00:34.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell if I know! You were the only \None here when they tossed us in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.80,0:00:36.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.24,0:00:40.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Lucy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.04,0:02:18.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.16,0:02:21.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.79,0:02:23.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A magic barrier, I reckon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.05,0:02:25.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Barrier...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.23,0:02:27.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't use magic in this cage,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.66,0:02:31.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and if you try damaging it with excessive force, \Nyou'll be knocked on your butt like you just were.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.65,0:02:35.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you're locked up in here, \Nit's like it's all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.21,0:02:36.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make me laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.91,0:02:40.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roar of the Fire Dragon... Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.10,0:02:45.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Real Nightmare!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.68,0:02:50.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Make a fool outta me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.67,0:02:51.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.86,0:02:52.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roar of the...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.93,0:02:54.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll do for a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.46,0:02:55.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll do!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.75,0:02:57.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That'll do it for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.60,0:02:59.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?! Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.59,0:03:01.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.50,0:03:06.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Meeting you here is surely a sign \Nfrom the god of evil, laddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.45,0:03:10.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's put our heads together and \Nthink up a way to escape from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.20,0:03:13.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:19.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is lucky that we met here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.49,0:03:20.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.04,0:03:23.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You and us are comrades!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.30,0:03:24.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And since we're comrades...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.85,0:03:27.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...let's have you put this on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.11,0:03:29.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's lame, so no thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.34,0:03:33.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Lame?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.24,0:03:37.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, more importantly, \Nwhy are you guys in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.38,0:03:41.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're here 'cause evil guys like \Nus don't know when to quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:44.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To be precise, where there's \Ntreasure, there's evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.73,0:03:48.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like the treasure you people \Nare looking for is that clock, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.21,0:03:51.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it has some \Nconnection to this cathedral!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.32,0:03:53.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. You did your homework.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.13,0:03:57.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Evil guys are plugged into a network of evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.04,0:03:59.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And so,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.28,0:04:01.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,we snuck into this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.77,0:04:04.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And then we heard something terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.76,0:04:06.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Something terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.17,0:04:13.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Holiness, about the \Narchbishop's madness...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.70,0:04:16.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps we can no longer keep it hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.87,0:04:19.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The pilgrims outside the gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:21.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems they don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:22.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.69,0:04:27.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All we need do is keep the archbishop out \Nof sight until the anniversary event begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.66,0:04:33.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If there are those who spread negative rumors, \Nthe Cleaner only need be sent to eliminate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.00,0:04:34.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Eliminate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.78,0:04:37.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That means kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.97,0:04:43.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought that was big trouble, and tried \Nto escape right away, but ended up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.12,0:04:48.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The only silver lining is they \Ndon't know what we overheard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:55.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But! If they do find out what we heard, \NI bet we'll never get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.06,0:04:59.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We may never get out...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.17,0:05:00.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.45,0:05:03.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! I thought evil doesn't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.82,0:05:08.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure, but what are we gonna \Ndo when magic won't even work here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.46,0:05:09.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm breakin' outta here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.27,0:05:13.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever happens, I gotta save Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.76,0:05:15.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, there's a guy \Nwhose ass I wanna kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.31,0:05:17.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Break out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.41,0:05:19.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds so evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.33,0:05:23.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a new evil milestone in the \Nannals of Jiggle Butt Gang history!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.76,0:05:27.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! If you guys wanna be saved \Ntoo, you better cooperate with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.85,0:05:30.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Leave the strategy to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.32,0:05:32.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lackeys, assemble!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.14,0:05:33.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.99,0:05:38.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...oughta be good training.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.79,0:05:44.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is goin' on here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:49.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's true that Michelle is \Nthe sixth member of Oracion Seis?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:52.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She fooled us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.65,0:05:53.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.27,0:05:57.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Natsu, Lucy, and the others \Nhave been captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.48,0:05:58.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:01.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all I could do \Njust to get away myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.96,0:06:03.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't blame yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.96,0:06:05.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not all your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:07.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cana. What do you want to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.92,0:06:13.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My cards didn't foretell that Brain II \Nwould show up at Kardia Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.95,0:06:17.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And they didn't give me accurate pairings \Neither for splitting into teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.61,0:06:20.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone was out of step \Nwith each other, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.23,0:06:21.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.91,0:06:23.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't mesh with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.81,0:06:27.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean someone or something \Nwas using your divinations?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.54,0:06:28.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:32.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez. This whole thing is frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.08,0:06:35.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, now isn't the time \Nto review our mistakes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.70,0:06:40.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more important to save Natsu-san and \NLucy-san, then do something about this situation!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.15,0:06:42.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Wendy's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.45,0:06:45.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, young lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.43,0:06:50.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the "Actually" people!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.15,0:06:52.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who might you folks be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.23,0:06:56.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we belong to the \NArchaeological Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.51,0:07:00.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we would like to meet with \NLucy Heartfilia-sama, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.20,0:07:03.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on? It's noisy out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.14,0:07:06.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What business do you have with Lucy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:08.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.45,0:07:11.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the master here, Macao.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.65,0:07:13.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would know your purpose in coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.61,0:07:15.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:17.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...it concerns an extremely important matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.81,0:07:20.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to speak with Lucy-sama directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.51,0:07:24.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite so! It has to do with that sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.21,0:07:29.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy and Natsu were both \Ncaptured by Oracion Seis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.03,0:07:30.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.65,0:07:32.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.64,0:07:35.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We would like to hear even \Na little information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:38.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, with circumstances continually changing,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.47,0:07:41.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose there's no longer any \Nreason to hide it, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.02,0:07:45.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, you know of Will Neville, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.55,0:07:49.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I am Jean-Luc Neville, \NWill's great-grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.62,0:07:53.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is unexpected...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.22,0:08:00.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I was on good terms with \NLucy-sama's father, Jude Heartfilia-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.27,0:08:05.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy's dad... This story is starting \Nto come together somehow...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:12.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I have devoted my life to seeing \Nthat the Infinity Clock stays sealed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.45,0:08:15.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a Celestial Spirit Wizard?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.36,0:08:18.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. As someone who has \Ninherited the Neville name,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.94,0:08:21.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just know the history \Nof the Infinity Clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.91,0:08:25.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My purpose is to give the warning \Nif there is a threat of chaos
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.35,0:08:28.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,spreading throughout the world and \Nto take precautions against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.15,0:08:31.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it happened several months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.93,0:08:38.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At the excavation site of certain ruins, a \Nhand of the Infinity Clock was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.68,0:08:43.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The ruins were there to \Nkeep magic sealed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.78,0:08:48.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, the Archaeological Society \Nreceived word from the expedition,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.51,0:08:51.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but by the time we got \Nthere, it was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.74,0:08:56.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, it had actually had \Nfallen into Jude's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.49,0:09:00.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, the clock hand possesses \Nan extremely high level of magic
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.44,0:09:01.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that is easy to track down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.49,0:09:06.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If it had fallen into the wrong hands, it's \Nvery likely that chaos would be summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.84,0:09:13.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was anxious, but when I found out at last \Nthat Jude-sama had it, I got in touch with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.61,0:09:19.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to seal away the magic that it was \Nemitting, I wrapped it in a magic cloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.43,0:09:25.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Jude-sama searched for another \Nsafe place to seal it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:27.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He made me that promise, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.87,0:09:34.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So my guess is that Lucy's father \Nmeant to entrust that to her...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.06,0:09:38.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How dangerous is the Infinity Clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.79,0:09:44.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's powerful magic that activates the \Nendless nightmare... Real Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.98,0:09:47.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Real Nightmare?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.80,0:09:52.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it controls the "sense \Nof time" that humans possess,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.67,0:09:55.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,thereby controlling time itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.83,0:09:57.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bit difficult to explain,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:10:01.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but it doesn't actually manipulate time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.00,0:10:04.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all a matter of the human sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.37,0:10:05.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.40,0:10:07.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ask me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.84,0:10:12.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The control of time is what's \Nmeant by "chaos will descend".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.14,0:10:15.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And that'll bring about the end of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:17.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm finding it hard to picture that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:21.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it. Right now is when, actually?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:24.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you actually doing right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.28,0:10:26.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is actually standing in front of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.49,0:10:30.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll lose the ability to comprehend \Nevery last bit of your own mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.08,0:10:36.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A person's memories and consciousness are actually an \Naccumulation of all of his or her experiences up to now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.47,0:10:40.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If the connection between all those \Ntimes are manipulated, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.29,0:10:42.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...you'd lose all sense of self.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.02,0:10:45.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's some serious stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.73,0:10:48.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Chaos" doesn't even begin to describe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.62,0:10:52.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Infinity Clock is in the \Nsky over Zentopia Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.78,0:10:56.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told that the roots of the \Nreligion's liturgy comes from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.58,0:10:59.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's said that the people who survived \Nthe chaos of the clock long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.84,0:11:02.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,are the ones who actually founded Zentopia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.26,0:11:07.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They sealed away the terror and have \Nwarned of it all along, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.68,0:11:12.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For a long time, its existence was \Nactually hidden from Zentopia's history,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.45,0:11:15.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but once every 100 years, the \Nmagic it accumulated was released,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.68,0:11:18.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,often making it the target of evildoers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.06,0:11:24.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm begging you. Please \Ntake this job, Fairy Tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.79,0:11:28.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop it... Stop the Infinity Clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.98,0:11:30.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need to be asked, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.68,0:11:31.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.65,0:11:34.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We have to save Natsu and Lucy, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.49,0:11:38.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. We'll accept this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.50,0:11:41.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fairy Tail will take care of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.28,0:11:47.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations on the restoration \Nof the Infinity Castle, Brain II!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.86,0:11:50.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been tough on you, huh, Klodoa?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.06,0:11:56.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no. All I did was follow \NMaster Zero's orders, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:12:04.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That being said, we've progressed this far \Nbecause of Master Zero's favorite thing, your skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.63,0:12:06.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed as always!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.74,0:12:10.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of that, this smart alec brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.39,0:12:15.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also impressive how \NImitatia-sama used her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.58,0:12:18.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Michelle... Tell me... Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.39,0:12:20.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.85,0:12:25.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Imitatia, not Michelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.59,0:12:27.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop making me tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.71,0:12:30.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a Celestial Spirit Wizard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.12,0:12:33.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The endless nightmare will begin...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.94,0:12:49.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that to seal the Infinity Clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.31,0:12:53.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Celestial Spirit Wizards were actually \Nutilizing a biological link, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.34,0:12:54.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We heard something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.05,0:12:59.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The new Oracion Seis was \Ncutting that link, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:01.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, if the link is severed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.75,0:13:05.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it seems the Celestial Spirit Wizard \Nis cursed with 100 years of sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.61,0:13:07.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and goes into a chrysalis-like state.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:09.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chrysalis?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.13,0:13:10.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.05,0:13:14.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The biological link takes \Npowerful magic to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.93,0:13:17.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so if it's severed by the Anti-Link,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.39,0:13:22.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the advance of time on the body and mind \Nbecomes extremely slow as a reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.99,0:13:25.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the person sleeps for 100 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.27,0:13:30.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sort of sacrifice so that we'll \Nbe able to control the Infinity Clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.24,0:13:33.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just like treating people as tools!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.06,0:13:34.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.94,0:13:39.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've already slept once for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.60,0:13:42.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's nothing compared to 100 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.79,0:13:48.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But even just seven years, I'll never forget \Nhow confusing and painful it was coming home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.26,0:13:53.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though time had passed for everyone \Nelse, we didn't spend any of it with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:56.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you understand that feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.32,0:14:01.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It made me think how \Ncruel it is to lose time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.72,0:14:05.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, we had friends who accepted us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.89,0:14:09.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did those Celestial Spirit Wizards \Nhave that same kind of support?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.02,0:14:12.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't, which is exactly \Nwhy it can be called a "curse".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.47,0:14:17.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be cursed the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.26,0:14:22.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Michelle, I was really happy when I met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.69,0:14:27.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing this for your sake, Nee-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.15,0:14:32.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying this is for my sake?! \NLying to me?! Getting close to me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.93,0:14:36.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't all a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.20,0:14:39.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What about my father?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.13,0:14:42.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you calling me Nee-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.28,0:14:44.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.24,0:14:52.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay. Let's can the chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.60,0:14:54.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Brain, let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.30,0:14:57.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea, Imitatia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.76,0:15:02.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucy Heartfilia, very shortly, \Nit will be time to say farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.17,0:15:07.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually very grateful \Nthat you accepted this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.57,0:15:09.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So Titania, please take this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.69,0:15:10.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.95,0:15:16.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, this was discovered in the \Nancient ruins along with the clock hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.67,0:15:20.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's said to keep evil at bay, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:27.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain that right now, you're actually \Nthe only one who can master this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.26,0:15:29.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright. I'll try to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.50,0:15:31.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.49,0:15:35.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, we shall also spare no effort \Nin doing whatever we can to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.49,0:15:38.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall continue researching ways to \Nattack the problem of Real Nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.33,0:15:41.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's reassuring, so yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.16,0:15:44.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how are we gonna storm the enemy camp?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.20,0:15:47.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No worries there. Reinforcements are coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.25,0:15:51.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you were able \Nto find that. Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.81,0:15:55.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's definitely a surveillance lacrima.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.16,0:15:58.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's repaired and the recorded footage \Nhas been restored as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.52,0:16:01.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Play it back right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.89,0:16:02.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.14,0:16:11.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the priest who periodically \Nvisited the members of Oracion Seis.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.48,0:16:16.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Freeze it! Enhance!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.93,0:16:17.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.46,0:16:20.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.48,0:16:24.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Cardinal Rapowant!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.44,0:16:27.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You... You were the one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.45,0:16:30.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, go big, old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.96,0:16:33.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Leave it to me, laddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.44,0:16:35.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lackeys, get in position!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.34,0:16:36.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.42,0:16:40.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Supersonic Jiggle Butt, begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.40,0:16:46.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.25,0:16:52.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go! Just one more effort!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.45,0:16:54.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't take a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.98,0:16:57.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is pretty tiring!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.65,0:16:59.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know your asses can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.91,0:17:02.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When it comes to flames that don't use \Nmagic, I'm sure you guys can pull it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.43,0:17:06.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Matter of fact, you idiots were the \Nones who came up with this plan,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.04,0:17:08.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so believe in yourselves and shake that ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:13.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the redesigned Christina!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.64,0:17:16.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Blue Pegasus...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.44,0:17:26.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.54,0:17:31.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Infinity Clock is in the sky. \NSo we have to get airborne, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.07,0:17:33.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not one of my favorite people, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.20,0:17:36.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you quit your grumbling \Nand get on board?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.49,0:17:38.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm stuck here minding the fort again?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.97,0:17:41.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My divination is on target this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.83,0:17:47.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We leave the attack to the handpicked \Nteam and do what we can do on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:51.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone! Let's get fired up \Nand begin making our attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.01,0:17:54.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's move out! Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.76,0:18:01.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Control this thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.77,0:18:03.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiya, is something wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.22,0:18:05.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The stern's taken damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.58,0:18:07.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take a look. Everyone, stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.86,0:18:09.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Men!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.32,0:18:10.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-chan! Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.32,0:18:14.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.37,0:18:17.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,More precisely, somebody broke it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.63,0:18:19.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.57,0:18:20.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An intruder...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.88,0:18:22.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.37,0:18:26.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oracion Seis...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.31,0:18:27.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Racer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.40,0:18:34.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard... Somehow, you sneaked \Non board. An impressive Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.17,0:18:36.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to... throw you overboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.84,0:18:37.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.13,0:18:41.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.26,0:18:48.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.60,0:18:51.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get you for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.30,0:18:53.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you... fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.45,0:18:54.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.76,0:19:00.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.87,0:19:03.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave him to me! Go back by everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.53,0:19:04.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.73,0:19:09.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.37,0:19:10.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Racer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.74,0:19:11.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mira...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.13,0:19:13.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ichiya! Go after Mira!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.94,0:19:16.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Men! Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.57,0:19:18.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave him to my sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.77,0:19:19.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.66,0:19:20.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.66,0:19:22.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind, just hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.23,0:19:23.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.10,0:19:26.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! First, repairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.42,0:19:27.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody, pitch in!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.86,0:19:28.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.70,0:19:31.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Mira.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.38,0:19:42.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going back there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.00,0:19:45.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.50,0:19:57.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you... You're not \Ngetting on that ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.82,0:20:03.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Brats... Survive and come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.58,0:20:06.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Kinana's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.48,0:20:07.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.08,0:20:09.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.35,0:20:13.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the other day, her \Nspells have gotten worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.39,0:20:14.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.86,0:20:17.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.86,0:20:18.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.94,0:20:21.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're calling me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.66,0:20:28.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're doin' it! More! More!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.11,0:20:31.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.11,0:20:35.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Fire! Somebody, help!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.96,0:20:37.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.75,0:20:40.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My butt's on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.31,0:20:41.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.84,0:20:44.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Help us! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:43.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.47,0:20:47.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Help us! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.10,0:20:49.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't allow this! The \Nfire extinguisher lacrima!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.29,0:20:51.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna let you people \Nout just temporarily...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:55.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.43,0:20:56.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, get out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.52,0:20:58.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.82,0:21:01.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.65,0:21:04.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Boss, this is no time to be moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.34,0:21:06.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Our butts are still on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.65,0:21:07.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.98,0:21:09.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll handle this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.88,0:21:13.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, our butts are on fire! \NIt'd be a waste not to use them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.20,0:21:15.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lackeys, fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.08,0:21:16.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.12,0:21:21.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gas-Butt Triple Ecstasy! Fire Special!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.82,0:21:26.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.30,0:21:27.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The fire's out, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.99,0:21:30.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is what you call killing \Ntwo birds with one stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.44,0:21:32.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm goin' straight to Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.72,0:21:35.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.95,0:21:39.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Coco! What are you doin' here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.87,0:21:41.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, she's gotta be a prisoner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.77,0:21:43.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take me with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.23,0:21:53.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That wizard broke out?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.84,0:21:55.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What shall we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.30,0:21:58.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.19,0:22:01.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Real Nightmare is going to be activated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.30,0:22:09.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The endless nightmare is beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.22,0:22:12.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Chaos...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.73,0:22:15.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cover the whole world...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.80,0:23:58.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening with Gray and Juvia lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.47,0:24:00.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in \Nthat half-naked bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.81,0:24:04.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. Then I wonder what's gonna \Nhappen with Elfman and Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.33,0:24:06.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know, don't care!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.00,0:24:10.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I guess it's what you \Nmight call Spiral of Love, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.79,0:24:13.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be better to \Nsay Labyrinth of Love?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.90,0:24:16.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Spiral of Time!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.04,0:24:19.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y'know, you don't have to bend over \Nbackwards to tie into the title.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.82,0:24:22.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't thinking about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.96,0:24:24.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't even look me in the eye!
